===Etymology===
Named after the Australian-born British thoracic surgeon Norman Barrett (1903–1979), who described it in 1950.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{lb|en|US|pathology}} An abnormal change ([[metaplasia]]) in the cells of the lower end of the [[esophagus]] thought to be caused by damage from chronic acid exposure, or [[reflux esophagitis]].

